permalink: /blog/conj1/
tags: inequality
categories: basics
related_posts: false
---

Let $A$ be a $n\times n$ positive semidefinite matrix. Then

$$
  \text{per}(A)^{2} \geq \text{per}(A \circ \Bar{A}),
$$

where $\text{per}(A)$ is the permanent of a matrix $A$, and $\circ$ denotes the Hadamard product.  
